<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for creating, editing and converting a chart in a PowerPoint slide.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to create charts in a presentation using PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Create, edit and convert more than 80 chart types.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Create custom charts by adding combinations from different chart types.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Convert individual chart in a PowerPoint slide to image.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Modify, include and remove chart elements like axes, label, legend and chart title.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Edit color for chart elements like chart area and plot area of an existing chart.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph><Bold>Note:</Bold> This library supports Chart creation, manipulation and conversion to PDF/image for .pptx format alone.</Paragraph>

